extends layout

block content
  h1= title

  ul
    - book_list.sort(function(a, b) {let textA = a.title.toUpperCase(); let textB = b.title.toUpperCase(); return (textA < textB) ? -1 : (textA > textB) ? 1 : 0;});
    each book in book_list
      li
        a(href=book.url) #{book.title}
        |  (#{book.author.name})

    else
      li There are no books.

//- 1. The records are sorted alphabetically using Array.sort()
//- 2. Then we display the title passed into the controller method - book_list
//- 3. We loop through the book_list records using each-in-else syntax - a list is created for each book displaying the title of the books and the name of the author. If there are no books the else is ran. 
//- 4. We make use of the pipe character for the author's name because to display the information onto 2 lines. also it separates the info of the book - the link and the author's name. 